wine = read_csv("./data/winequality-red.csv") %>% 
  janitor::clean_names() %>% 
  na.omit() %>% 
  as.data.frame()
## Parsed with column specification:
## cols(
##   `fixed acidity` = col_double(),
##   `volatile acidity` = col_double(),
##   `citric acid` = col_double(),
##   `residual sugar` = col_double(),
##   chlorides = col_double(),
##   `free sulfur dioxide` = col_double(),
##   `total sulfur dioxide` = col_double(),
##   density = col_double(),
##   pH = col_double(),
##   sulphates = col_double(),
##   alcohol = col_double(),
##   quality = col_double()
## )
trRows = createDataPartition(wine$quality, p = .75, list = F)

train_data = wine[trRows,]
test_data = wine[-trRows,]

Linear Kernel

ctrl <- trainControl(method = "cv")

set.seed(1)
svml.fit <- train(quality~., 
                  data = train_data, 
                  method = "svmLinear2",
                  preProcess = c("center", "scale"),
                  tuneGrid = data.frame(cost = exp(seq(-10,-5,len=20))),
                  trControl = ctrl)

ggplot(svml.fit, highlight = TRUE)

Radial Kernel

svmr.grid <- expand.grid(C = exp(seq(-1,4,len=10)),
                         sigma = exp(seq(-6,-2,len=10)))
set.seed(1)             
svmr.fit <- train(quality~., wine, 
                  subset = trRows,
                  method = "svmRadial",
                  preProcess = c("center", "scale"),
                  tuneGrid = svmr.grid,
                  trControl = ctrl)

ggplot(svmr.fit, highlight = TRUE)

Resample

resamp <- resamples(list(svmr = svmr.fit, svml = svml.fit))
